This article is a presidential notice from September 21, 2009, concerning national security. It states that according to the National Emergencies Act, a national emergency automatically terminates unless the President publishes a notice stating that it will continue. The notice declares that the national emergency with respect to persons who commit, threaten to commit, or support terrorism will continue beyond September 23, 2009. The President cites the grave acts of terrorism committed by foreign terrorists, including the September 11, 2001 attacks, as well as the ongoing threat of further attacks on the United States. The President determines that the national emergency and comprehensive sanctions are necessary to respond to this threat.